# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
I believe this issue is caused by package `webpack: 3.11.0` which is being used in `@angular/cli: 1.7.4`.

### Description

Not the best description but... Putting an angular-elements app into an angular v5 app simply does not work.

## üî• Exception or Error
The following is the error shown on the console which points to the bundled javascript from the angular-element app inside of the angular v5 app.

![error](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11788477/63181822-0b713b00-c01f-11e9-8bbb-dbb6e83deeeb.png)

<pre><code>Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read property 'bind' of undefined</code></pre>

## üåç  Your Environment

**Angular Version:**
<pre><code>
Angular CLI: 1.7.4
Node: 10.15.0
OS: darwin x64
Angular: 5.2.11
... animations, common, compiler, compiler-cli, core, forms
... http, language-service, platform-browser
... platform-browser-dynamic, router

@angular/cli: 1.7.4
@angular-devkit/build-optimizer: 0.3.2
@angular-devkit/core: 0.3.2
@angular-devkit/schematics: 0.3.2
@ngtools/json-schema: 1.2.0
@ngtools/webpack: 1.10.2
@schematics/angular: 0.3.2
@schematics/package-update: 0.3.2
typescript: 2.7.2
webpack: 3.11.0
</code></pre>

**Anything else relevant?**

- Is there a way to run the latest version (or at least v4) of `webpack` in an Angular v5 app? Is there a way to build the angular-elements app so that it doesn't depend on `window["webpackJsonp"]` returning an array?
 
- This issue is the one which makes me believe that the issue might be with the webpack version -- https://github.com/webpack/webpack/issues/6985
- Angular elements works perfectly with an Angular v6 app -- which is using webpack version 4.
- Angular elements app version I am using:
<pre><code>
Angular CLI: 8.0.6
Node: 10.15.0
OS: darwin x64
Angular: 8.0.3
... animations, common, compiler, compiler-cli, core, forms
... language-service, platform-browser, platform-browser-dynamic
... router

Package                           Version
-----------------------------------------------------------
@angular-devkit/architect         0.800.6
@angular-devkit/build-angular     0.800.6
@angular-devkit/build-optimizer   0.800.6
@angular-devkit/build-webpack     0.800.6
@angular-devkit/core              8.0.6
@angular-devkit/schematics        8.0.6
@angular/cli                      8.0.6
@angular/elements                 8.2.2
@ngtools/webpack                  8.0.6
@schematics/angular               8.0.6
@schematics/update                0.800.6
rxjs                              6.4.0
typescript                        3.4.5
webpack                           4.30.0
</code></pre>

Don't use `Array` constructor with the size value (ex. `new Array(5)`) - this will create a `HOLEY_ELEMENTS` array (even if this array is filled in later on!);

https://v8.dev/blog/elements-kinds
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/32054170/how-to-resize-an-array

#### Reproduction
I need to dynamically pass a component into a dialog and it must be rendered.

I have an object, with several components, example:
```javascript
{
        title: 'Vimbo Countdown',
        content: `<vimbo-countdown eventDate="2040-07-28"></vimbo-countdown>`
}
```

When the user clicks on the title, he opens a dialog and renders what is inside the content.
it is including in html, but not rendering, as if it does not understand the component.

my dialog html:
```html
<div class="dialog-content-wrapper">

    <mat-toolbar matDialogTitle class="mat-accent m-0">
        <mat-toolbar-row>
            <span class="title dialog-title">{{title}}</span>
        </mat-toolbar-row>
    </mat-toolbar>

    <div mat-dialog-content class="p-24 m-0" vimboPerfectScrollbar>
        <div [innerHTML]="content"></div>
    </div>

    <div mat-dialog-actions class="m-0 p-16" fxLayout="row" fxLayoutAlign="end center">
        <button mat-button (click)="matDialogRef.close()" class="mat-accent" aria-label="Close">
            CLOSE
        </button>
    </div>

</div>
```

my dialog component:
```javascript
import { Component, ViewEncapsulation, Inject } from '@angular/core';
import { MatDialogRef, MAT_DIALOG_DATA } from '@angular/material/dialog';
import { DomSanitizer, SafeHtml } from '@angular/platform-browser';

@Component({
    selector: 'developer-knowledge-base-article',
    templateUrl: './article.component.html',
    styleUrls: ['./article.component.scss'],
    encapsulation: ViewEncapsulation.None
})
export class KnowledgeBaseArticleComponent {

    public content: SafeHtml;
    public title: SafeHtml;

    /**
     * Constructor
     *
     * @param {MatDialogRef<KnowledgeBaseArticleComponent>} matDialogRef
     * @param {MAT_DIALOG_DATA}_data
     * @param {DomSanitizer} domSanitizer
     */
    constructor(
        public matDialogRef: MatDialogRef<KnowledgeBaseArticleComponent>,
        @Inject(MAT_DIALOG_DATA) public _data: any,
        private domSanitizer: DomSanitizer
    ) {
        console.log(_data);
        this.content = this.domSanitizer.bypassSecurityTrustHtml(_data.article.content);
        this.title = _data.article.title;
    }
}
```

In the html dialog, inspecting is appearing, but it doesn't work, like anywhere else in the app
![Captura de Tela_selecionar √°rea_20190814200309](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11314585/63062238-8d058380-bece-11e9-9daa-cf71fe924acc.png)


if it had rendered correctly, the html would look something like the image below.
![Captura de Tela_selecionar √°rea_20190814200415](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11314585/63062291-b4f4e700-bece-11e9-8921-3ea2ec19ddf2.png)

and the component, I'm important at the root of the module
```javascript
@NgModule({
    declarations: [
        DeveloperKnowledgeBaseComponent,
        KnowledgeBaseArticleComponent
    ],
    imports: [
        RouterModule.forChild(routes),

        MatButtonModule,
        MatDialogModule,
        MatIconModule,
        MatListModule,
        MatToolbarModule,

        VimboSharedModule,

        VimboCountdownModule,
        VimboHighlightModule
    ],
    providers: [DeveloperKnowledgeBaseService],
    entryComponents: [
        KnowledgeBaseArticleComponent
    ]
})
```
